T1  - Clearing, settlement and monetary policy
AU  - Lacker, Jeffrey M.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 40
IS  - 2
SP  - 347
EP  - 381
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/10/01/
T2  - Monetary Policy and Financial Markets
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0304-3932(97)00046-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393297000469
KW  - Monetary policy
AB  - This paper develops a general equilibrium model of the clearing and settlement of private payment instruments. Spatial separation, heterogeneous preference shocks and limited communication provide a role for private credit as a means of payment. Although this method could be applied to various settlement arrangements, the use of central bank deposit liabilities in settlement is studied here. Various tools of payment system policy, such as intraday overdraft limits and fees, collateral requirements, reserve requirements, and interest on reserves, are examined.
ER  - 

